      • walkAll

        public boolean walkAll()
        Description copied from interface: Equivalents.EquivalentWalker
        Specifies whether we should walk all peers, or stop when a peer does not match.

        In other words, return true to evaluate all peers, even when null is returned from Equivalents.EquivalentWalker.locate(Object, Named), and return false to stop walking (in that direction) once Equivalents.EquivalentWalker.locate(Object, Named) returns null.

        Specified by:
        walkAll in interface Equivalents.EquivalentWalker<Rule,N extends Named>
        Returns:
        Whether all peers should be walked, or if we should stop walking a direction once a peer does not match.
